<article>
    <h1>THE SUL&#xAD;TAN&#x2019;S EX&#xAD;PE&#xAD;RI&#xAD;ENCE AT SUL&#xAD;TANS OF SHAVE</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201225/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-12-25"><time>2020-12-25</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE STYLE</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Toss your dinky bath­room ra­zor and in­dulge in a pam­per­ing shave at groom­ing stal­wart Sul­tans of Shave.</p>
    <p>The lo­cal brand of­fers a se­lec­tion of hair­cuts, shaves and pack­ages ad­min­is­tered by a team of gen­tle­men’s bar­bers.</p>
    <p>The crowd favourite, Sul­tan’s Shave, is priced at $65 for a five-step shave com­pris­ing fa­cial scrub, hot and cold towel, post-shave balm and mois­turiser.</p>
    <p>Or spring for the full works with The Sul­tan’s Ex­pe­ri­ence ($130) that com­bines the Sul­tan’s Shave with a Sul­tan’s Hair­cut (usu­ally $75).</p>
    <p>Treat­ing dad as well? The store of­fers a Fa­ther & Son pack­age at $180, com­pris­ing a Deluxe Shave and Deluxe Hair­cut for two.</p>
    <p>For an ex­tra novel ex­pe­ri­ence, take a seat at the brand’s new­est out­let, which opened in the mid­dle of last year in Jewel Changi</p>
    <p>Air­port, with domed ceil­ings and hues of blue and gold that make you feel like true roy­alty.</p>
    <p>Info: 04-240 Jewel Changi</p>
    <p>Air­port, 78 Air­port Boule­vard. To book, call 6388-0201 or go to sul­tan­sof­shave.com</p>

